    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "## Do This:\r\n\r\nYou're working on a digital assistant that reminds users to think critically when using AI tools. Every time the assistant starts up, it prints a two-line reminder message. Right now, the same block is repeated over and over. Your task is to clean up the code using a function.\r\n\r\n1. Read the block of repeated code.\r\n\r\n2. Create a function called `ai_reminder()` that prints both lines.\r\n\r\n3. Replace the repeated block by calling your new function three times.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n<i class=\"fa-solid fa-laptop\"></i> **Coding Tip**\r\n\r\nYour function can include more than one line of code -- just make sure each line is indented the same amount under the `def` statement.\r\n\r\nUse the UMPIRE strategy:\r\n\r\n* **U**nderstand: What message are you repeating?\r\n\r\n* **M**ake a plan: What should your function do?\r\n\r\n* **P**roduce: Define the function and replace the repetition.\r\n\r\n* **I**nspect: Does it still print the message three times?\r\n\r\n* **E**xplain: Why is using a function better in this case?",
